Class ProductNameSearch

    public class ProductNameSearch
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISearchingEngine

    The class of ProductNameSearch is used to abstractly define the type of the instances.

    ISearchingEngine implementation providing instances are able to filter Products by it's name.

      • ProductNameSearch

        public ProductNameSearch​(ProductsContainer container,
                         boolean exactSearch)

        Sets the container to be searching in. Then it sets the boolean value of exactSearch - it defines if the value has to be same exactly to be the product name evaluated as possibly looked for.

        Parameters:
        container - the container of the products
        exactSearch - if the word match has to be 100%, or just containing one another is wanted

        public java.util.List<Product> search​(java.lang.String findingBy)

        Provides searching in the ProductsContainer instance.

        This kind of searcher provides going through all the given Products from the product container and picks all those with corresponding name.

        Specified by:
